286
00:12:23,120 --> 00:12:24,160
I know what happened this morning

287
00:12:24,160 --> 00:12:25,120
You were on purpose

288
00:12:25,640 --> 00:12:26,240
I hope from now on,

289
00:12:26,240 --> 00:12:27,680
nothing like that happens again.

290
00:12:29,680 --> 00:12:30,960
Do you think I’m that bad?

291
00:12:31,680 --> 00:12:32,520
You clearly have a problem with me

292
00:12:34,080 --> 00:12:34,640
I don’t.

293
00:12:36,560 --> 00:12:37,520
Don't even try to deny it.

294
00:12:40,400 --> 00:12:41,800
Since you came here to talk,

295
00:12:42,320 --> 00:12:43,840
let’s be honest with each other.

296
00:12:43,840 --> 00:12:45,080
Isn't better to just clear the air?

297
00:12:45,920 --> 00:12:46,640
Are you sure?

298
00:12:47,880 --> 00:12:48,480
Go ahead.

299
00:12:50,040 --> 00:12:50,960
What's your problem with me?

300
00:12:52,120 --> 00:12:52,880
You’re unprofessional.

301
00:12:53,920 --> 00:12:54,680
You don't memorize your lines.

302
00:12:55,520 --> 00:12:56,280
I can explain that.

303
00:12:56,520 --> 00:12:57,280
Your acting is terrible.

304
00:12:57,400 --> 00:12:58,160
You show up late and leave early.

305
00:12:58,520 --> 00:12:59,360
You have no work ethic.

306
00:13:01,240 --> 00:13:02,320
No work ethic?

307
00:13:03,920 --> 00:13:05,440
Fine. Now it's my turn.

308
00:13:05,840 --> 00:13:06,720
Go on.

309
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:08,640
Fine, I'll tell it.

310
00:13:09,400 --> 00:13:10,560
You pull the seniority card.

311
00:13:10,840 --> 00:13:11,440
You’re rigid.

312
00:13:11,520 --> 00:13:12,040
I’m old?

313
00:13:12,640 --> 00:13:13,520
You’re not just old,

314
00:13:13,800 --> 00:13:15,000
you’re condescending.

315
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:15,840
You’re such a poser.

316
00:13:15,920 --> 00:13:17,360
Not only is your acting bad,

317
00:13:17,720 --> 00:13:18,600
but you’re narcissistic.

318
00:13:18,760 --> 00:13:19,920
You have no public decency.

319
00:13:20,040 --> 00:13:21,880
Well, you’re arrogant, conceited, and have zero empathy!

320
00:13:22,080 --> 00:13:22,680
I...

321
00:13:23,360 --> 00:13:24,280
And you have small eyes!

322
00:13:24,400 --> 00:13:25,680
That’s a personal attack!

323
00:13:26,120 --> 00:13:28,600
It’s an objective description.

324
00:13:31,400 --> 00:13:32,080
Xu Xinglang,

325
00:13:32,880 --> 00:13:34,000
Do you really think...

326
00:13:34,560 --> 00:13:35,480
you’re that hot?

327
00:13:37,800 --> 00:13:38,640
Your eyes might be big,

328
00:13:39,600 --> 00:13:40,880
but they’re soulless.

329
00:13:41,080 --> 00:13:42,440
Your gaze is vacant.

330
00:13:42,440 --> 00:13:44,280
You look like a deformed goldfish in a tank.

331
00:13:46,280 --> 00:13:47,600
You’re not much better yourself!

332
00:13:47,920 --> 00:13:49,080
When you smile,

333
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:51,280
your mouth stretches all the way back to your molars.

334
00:13:51,480 --> 00:13:52,600
Like a catfish.

335
00:13:57,080 --> 00:13:58,760
You’re so childish, Xu Xinglang.

336
00:13:59,400 --> 00:14:00,600
Right back at you.

337
00:14:00,960 --> 00:14:02,080
Teacher Jian Mo,

338
00:14:02,560 --> 00:14:04,240
you’re capable of personal attacks too.

339
00:14:04,920 --> 00:14:06,160
You attacked me first.

340
00:14:08,640 --> 00:14:09,280
It seems...

341
00:14:09,280 --> 00:14:10,600
...we’ve finally laid it all out.

342
00:14:11,400 --> 00:14:12,360
Anything else you're unhappy about?

343
00:14:14,760 --> 00:14:16,040
From now on, the volume of your music...

344
00:14:16,920 --> 00:14:18,000
Can you keep it down?

345
00:14:18,400 --> 00:14:19,200
Ok.

346
00:14:19,640 --> 00:14:20,400
No problem.

347
00:14:20,960 --> 00:14:21,840
And...

348
00:14:23,880 --> 00:14:24,920
Next time you see me,

349
00:14:25,320 --> 00:14:26,480
Could you stop being so stone-faced

350
00:14:27,440 --> 00:14:28,240
It’s not on purpose.

351
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:30,920
I just have social anxiety.

352
00:14:35,400 --> 00:14:36,840
I guess we’re done talking?

353
00:14:37,280 --> 00:14:38,120
Mr.Jian,

354
00:14:38,960 --> 00:14:41,600
since neither of us is a saint,

355
00:14:42,360 --> 00:14:43,080
how about

356
00:14:43,200 --> 00:14:44,840
we just tolerate each other?

357
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:45,920
Fine.

358
00:14:47,280 --> 00:14:48,600
Then, here’s to a happy collaboration.

359
00:14:50,720 --> 00:14:51,320
Teacher

360
00:14:51,600 --> 00:14:52,560
you forgot,

361
00:14:52,920 --> 00:14:54,280
we still have to read the script.

362
00:14:56,600 --> 00:14:57,440
Alright.

363
00:15:02,600 --> 00:15:03,440
Let's start.

364
00:15:04,840 --> 00:15:05,680
Which line?

365
00:15:09,640 --> 00:15:10,640
I’m not running away.

366
00:15:11,640 --> 00:15:12,560
I’m just...

367
00:15:13,240 --> 00:15:14,000
Just...

368
00:15:14,720 --> 00:15:15,480
Just...

369
00:15:15,800 --> 00:15:16,200
Just...

370
00:15:16,320 --> 00:15:17,080
Hold on.

371
00:15:19,560 --> 00:15:20,440
What are you doing?

372
00:15:22,880 --> 00:15:23,680
Li Fang said...

373
00:15:24,160 --> 00:15:25,280
those three "justs"

374
00:15:25,520 --> 00:15:26,640
have three layers of emotion.

375
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:29,000
It’s not like that.

376
00:15:29,400 --> 00:15:30,280
Just be natural.

377
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:31,960
Don't force it so much.

378
00:15:35,240 --> 00:15:36,640
I’m not running away.

379
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:38,880
I’m just...

380
00:15:39,880 --> 00:15:40,600
Just...

381
00:15:42,080 --> 00:15:43,360
I’m just afraid I’ll lose you.

382
00:15:46,840 --> 00:15:48,360
Afraid that one day you'll leave me.

383
00:15:50,080 --> 00:15:51,600
Do you understand?

384
00:15:54,800 --> 00:15:55,880
If I said...

385
00:15:57,920 --> 00:15:59,200
we’ll never be apart again...

386
00:16:01,240 --> 00:16:02,080
Would you be willing?

387
00:16:11,440 --> 00:16:12,640
Are you really that afraid of me?

388
00:16:13,840 --> 00:16:14,320
You...

389
00:16:15,320 --> 00:16:16,040
...hate me?

390
00:16:17,360 --> 00:16:18,520
I’m just not used to it.

391
00:16:23,160 --> 00:16:24,080
Let’s try it again.

392
00:16:25,560 --> 00:16:26,480
I’ll read my lines.

393
00:16:27,400 --> 00:16:28,040
You

394
00:16:28,600 --> 00:16:29,720
don't think of me as Xu Xinglang.

395
00:16:30,520 --> 00:16:31,240
Okay?

396
00:16:40,120 --> 00:16:41,440
I’m not running away.

397
00:16:43,160 --> 00:16:44,080
I’m just...

398
00:16:45,200 --> 00:16:46,120
Just...

399
00:16:47,560 --> 00:16:49,160
just afraid of losing you.

400
00:16:51,120 --> 00:16:51,840
Do you...

401
00:16:52,360 --> 00:16:53,480
...understand?

402
00:16:58,360 --> 00:17:00,040
Do you remember who I am?

403
00:17:01,320 --> 00:17:02,400
I’m a assassin.

404
00:17:03,320 --> 00:17:04,599
And you’re my boss.

405
00:17:07,200 --> 00:17:08,520
Until my mission is complete,

406
00:17:09,240 --> 00:17:11,240
we will never be apart.

407
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:15,000
Never apart.

408
00:17:16,480 --> 00:17:17,640
Are you willing?

409
00:17:24,560 --> 00:17:26,280
Never to be apart again.

410
00:17:30,320 --> 00:17:31,320
Xinglang

411
00:17:33,080 --> 00:17:34,480
Did I come back

412
00:17:34,920 --> 00:17:35,680
at a bad time?

413
00:17:36,360 --> 00:17:36,880
No.

414
00:17:37,240 --> 00:17:37,760
We

415
00:17:38,640 --> 00:17:39,200
were rehearsing.

416
00:17:39,800 --> 00:17:40,400
I see.

417
00:17:40,640 --> 00:17:41,400
I’ll just drop this off and go.

418
00:17:41,720 --> 00:17:42,240
Carry on.

419
00:17:42,240 --> 00:17:42,680
No need.

420
00:17:43,400 --> 00:17:43,880
I have things to do.

421
00:17:44,520 --> 00:17:45,120
I’m leaving.

422
00:17:46,200 --> 00:17:46,600
Well...

423
00:17:48,040 --> 00:17:48,440
He’s gone.

424
00:17:54,320 --> 00:17:55,440
I really shouldn't have come back.

425
00:18:00,560 --> 00:18:01,160
Morning.

426
00:18:01,920 --> 00:18:02,520
Morning.

427
00:18:04,080 --> 00:18:04,720
How are the preparations for today?

428
00:18:05,680 --> 00:18:06,440
All ready.

429
00:18:06,920 --> 00:18:07,680
We can start.

430
00:18:08,560 --> 00:18:09,240
Let's go.

431
00:18:14,640 --> 00:18:15,320
Master Gu

432
00:18:16,120 --> 00:18:17,080
Who’s that girl?

433
00:18:17,560 --> 00:18:18,320
She’s pretty.

434
00:18:19,160 --> 00:18:20,080
Someone very important to me.

435
00:18:20,480 --> 00:18:21,400
Come on, let's get started.

436
00:18:25,760 --> 00:18:26,680
Let's get it rolling

437
00:18:31,280 --> 00:18:32,520
Yes, yes, yes.

438
00:18:32,640 --> 00:18:34,000
Closer.

439
00:18:35,200 --> 00:18:36,160
Yes, just like that.

440
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:38,440
Good, good. Perfect!

441
00:18:48,960 --> 00:18:49,840
Great.

442
00:18:53,280 --> 00:18:54,800
Give me even more.

443
00:18:58,600 --> 00:18:59,960
Pleasure working with you.

444
00:19:06,120 --> 00:19:06,840
We got it.

445
00:19:12,480 --> 00:19:13,920
You both did a great job.

446
00:19:14,520 --> 00:19:15,560
It’s been a pleasure.

447
00:19:19,160 --> 00:19:19,640
Excuse me,

448
00:19:19,760 --> 00:19:20,640
I need to use the restroom.

449
00:19:24,360 --> 00:19:25,160
The shoot is finished.

450
00:19:27,080 --> 00:19:27,560
Master Gu

451
00:19:27,560 --> 00:19:28,200
Take a look at the photos.

452
00:19:28,680 --> 00:19:29,320
come on

453
00:19:42,160 --> 00:19:42,960
Xinglang!

454
00:19:43,160 --> 00:19:45,240
Brilliant, absolutely brilliant.

455
00:19:46,200 --> 00:19:47,560
I saw the photos.

456
00:19:47,760 --> 00:19:49,280
The vibe is just off the charts.

457
00:19:49,800 --> 00:19:51,200
Producer Li shared the photos to the director too.

458
00:19:51,600 --> 00:19:53,160
He couldn't stop praising them.

459
00:19:53,360 --> 00:19:53,760
He said

460
00:19:53,920 --> 00:19:55,400
That’s exactly the feeling he wanted.

461
00:19:58,600 --> 00:20:00,080
As long as everyone is satisfied

462
00:20:00,400 --> 00:20:03,520
all our efforts are worthwhile.

463
00:20:06,280 --> 00:20:06,680
Xinglang,

464
00:20:07,360 --> 00:20:08,160
that night

465
00:20:08,840 --> 00:20:09,840
what did you and Jian Mo

466
00:20:10,280 --> 00:20:11,160
actually talk about?

467
00:20:12,240 --> 00:20:13,080
We...

468
00:20:13,200 --> 00:20:14,240
didn't really talk about much.

469
00:20:14,480 --> 00:20:15,080
Why?

470
00:20:15,280 --> 00:20:16,240
It’s just that the next day,

471
00:20:16,240 --> 00:20:17,320
the shoot went so smoothly.

472
00:20:17,440 --> 00:20:18,240
The vibe was so right.

473
00:20:18,560 --> 00:20:19,960
I thought you two had a heart-to-heart conversation

474
00:20:20,560 --> 00:20:21,600
and became best friends.

475
00:20:22,880 --> 00:20:23,760
The two of us?

476
00:20:24,040 --> 00:20:24,800
Forget it.

477
00:20:25,640 --> 00:20:27,200
We are polar opposites.

478
00:20:27,400 --> 00:20:28,080
Two different species.

479
00:20:28,920 --> 00:20:29,640
So who’s "high" and who’s "low"?

480
00:20:30,160 --> 00:20:30,520
Obviously, I’m the one on top.

481
00:20:31,400 --> 00:20:32,520
What are you even thinking?

482
00:20:33,200 --> 00:20:34,640
I have to say,

483
00:20:35,720 --> 00:20:36,560
I’m starting to ship you two.

484
00:20:37,120 --> 00:20:38,280
What’s going on?

485
00:20:38,640 --> 00:20:39,320
Is it just me?

486
00:20:42,880 --> 00:20:43,440
I think

487
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:44,640
I can smell

488
00:20:44,720 --> 00:20:46,320
something romantic in the air.

489
00:20:49,120 --> 00:20:49,760
Buddy,

490
00:20:50,160 --> 00:20:51,800
this is a restroom.

491
00:20:52,320 --> 00:20:54,120
The only thing you smell is the drain.

492
00:20:55,160 --> 00:20:55,720
Restroom.

493
00:20:56,200 --> 00:20:57,200
Drain.

494
00:20:57,840 --> 00:20:58,520
Don't walk away!

495
00:20:58,960 --> 00:21:00,320
Don't forget the opening ceremony tomorrow.

496
00:21:00,320 --> 00:21:02,320
I haven't gone over the schedule with you yet!

497
00:21:06,960 --> 00:21:07,360
Boss.

498
00:21:08,560 --> 00:21:09,200
Xinglang.

499
00:21:09,640 --> 00:21:10,120
Everything's smooth.

500
00:21:10,240 --> 00:21:10,960
Very smooth.

501
00:21:11,680 --> 00:21:12,600
The crew starts shooting tomorrow.

502
00:21:12,960 --> 00:21:14,280
Xu Xinglang is flying to Shanghai tonight

503
00:21:14,480 --> 00:21:15,960
to discuss his song recording session.

504
00:21:16,600 --> 00:21:16,920
But,

505
00:21:16,960 --> 00:21:18,360
the opening ceremony is tomorrow.

506
00:21:18,480 --> 00:21:19,560
He can just rush back afterward.

507
00:21:19,640 --> 00:21:20,320
Stop arguing with me.

508
00:21:20,760 --> 00:21:21,440
The company...

509
00:21:21,440 --> 00:21:22,640
is investing a fortune in this.

510
00:21:22,760 --> 00:21:23,120
Well...

511
00:21:23,880 --> 00:21:24,200
Hello?

512
00:21:29,400 --> 00:21:30,760
Talk about putting the agent in a tough spot.
